post_text:
Do you have a child who will be 4 years old before September 1, 2020? If you live within the School District of Lancaster boundaries, they are eligible for our PreK program. Even though our school year is starting virtually for students, our PreK children will receive weekly educational activities, daily opportunities to interact virtually with their teacher and classmates, as well as monthly supplemental supplies and activities to promote their education at home. Please complete the application at https://sdlancaster.org/enroll-your-child/pre-kindergarten-application/

Please note that spaces are limited, and enrollment is based on need, not on a first come, first served basis.

The Committee of the Whole Meeting will take place at 6:30 this evening in the Media Center at McCaskey East High School. Based on the Governor's directive, we cannot have more than 25 people in the meeting room. We will allow individuals who wish to comment into the room one-by-one in order to not exceed the limit. Everyone must wear a face covering and practice social distancing.

If you do not feel comfortable attending the meeting, you may provide feedback to the board, regarding the reopening plan, via email at schoolboard@sdlancaster.org.

As always, you can watch the meeting live at https://video.ibm.com/channel/9FJWFahd9NE.

Enjoy the amazing artwork of our McCaskey High School Campus seniors! üé®

Every year the high school art department features the artwork of our seniors in an exhibition opened to the public. For the first time ever, McCaskey High School Campus is presenting a virtual Senior Art Show. The artwork you will be viewing is by students with a concentration in art, as well as, seniors who may have taken art as an elective class. Enjoy the show!

To view this show full screen: open the link, look in the top right area for the work "present" and click on the arrow to the left of it. Some of these students have work for sale. If you are interested in purchasing any of this artwork, contact Lisa Wolf at lbwolf@lancaster.k12.pa.us.

May 4-8 is Teacher Appreciation Week. Show your favorite teacher or staff member how much you care today through a gift to the Lancaster Education Foundation!

With your gift of $25 or more, LEF will provide a book to your teacher's school library and a certificate to your teacher. Donations benefit students in all SDoL schools through teacher grants, educational programs, and scholarships.

Please include your name, teacher's name and the school in the special instructions or comments space.

**************************

Send a Message of Appreciation
Let your teacher know how much you care about him or her. Please include your name, teacher's name, and school.

Messages of appreciation can be sent through LEF@sdlancaster.org

post_text:
A Message from the McCaskey Alumni Association: Dear Friends of McCaskey High School,

Here is our Alumni Vidette Extra, a digital supplement to our signature publication, the Alumni Vidette, which members of the McCaskey Alumni Association receive a subscription to.

This challenging time has clarified the value of community connectedness. Though our Alumni Vidette Extra has been shared exclusively with members until today, the McCaskey Alumni Association now offers it freely and will continue to do so beyond Covid-19 in the interest of our unified McCaskey Pride.

Readers of this supplement who are not already MAA members will discover how they can subscribe to our 16-page Alumni Vidette, the only publication of, by, and for McCaskey alumni. Also outlined herein are ways you can assist SDoL families as they navigate the Covid-19 crisis.

#TornadoSTRONG

post_text: Calling all McCaskey High School Campus seniors! Your participation is requested for a local project. Read more below!
shared_text:
Dawn Cox is in Lancaster, Pennsylvania.
April 19 at 8:12 AM ¬∑ Instagram ¬∑

So proud of Georgia...she is documenting history through the McCaskey Seniors of COVID 19 in a ‚ÄúI was supposed to...‚Äù project. Here are a few out-take photos. She is planning to use the photos as a gift to them and/or an art exhibit of some kind in the future so we all remember them. If you are a McCaskey senior ...she would love to include you. Stringent safety protocols in place and only takes about two minutes. She hopes to get as many seniors as possible to fully represent the class of 2020. She has 10 ‚Äúappointments‚Äù today, but a few more spots open today, tomorrow and this week. DM Georgia (@georgia_is__ ) or me for more details. ***Georgia is sensitive to the fact that lives are being lost due to COVID 19 and how awful all of this is***but this is a pandemic passion project for her peer group and we are so proud of her. @ Lancaster, Pennsylvania

During this unprecedented time we are all still puzzled of what‚Äôs going on and how to handle things. A lot of times we read about things that are happening in the world but we are able to go on with our lives. This time it‚Äôs different, it has literally affected all of us especially in our day to day lives.

With schools closed and so many kids not having access to their daily lunch provided by the schools. The House of Pizza would like to provide a free slice of pizza and drink for all school age kids. Students stop in Monday-Friday between 11-1 and ask for your school lunch. Unfortunately you‚Äôll have to take it to go. We will do this until 4/3. Please feel free to stop in. Stay safe and stay healthy. #lancasterstrong Ôøº

God Bless

post_text: We are getting a lot of understandable questions about when school is scheduled to resume, now that Gov. Wolf extended the closure. According to the Department of Education, staff may return after April 6 with students to follow as early as April 9. As you know, that‚Äôs right before a scheduled four-day weekend for us. There is also the possibility the closure will be extended further. With so much uncertainty, it is difficult to determine a firm date. We are hopeful it is in April‚Äîbut only if it is safe and wise to return. We will let you know as soon as we know. Thank you for your continued patience and understanding!

Reminder: There is a Special Meeting to address the School Board Vacancy and any other matter that may come before the board tonight from 6:30 pm - 7:30 pm.

The School District of Lancaster Board of Directors will meet virtually. Per state law, any member of the public may attend in person. However, the board urges members of the public to consider practicing social distancing and view the meeting online here: https://video.ibm.com/channel/9FJWFahd9NE.

The public may comment concerning the vacancy prior to the board vote. Members of the public viewing online may make comments electronically through the livestream platform. Comments will be read aloud at the meeting if the commenting individuals provide name and address. Public comments, including electronic comments, are not part of a Q&A, nor will the board respond directly.

Agenda: https://bit.ly/2UuGcHj

post_text: We are hearing rumors in the community that we are discontinuing our meal service. These rumors are false! Our food distribution continues at five sites throughout the district (JP McCaskey, Hand, Reynolds, Carter & MacRae and Hamilton) on Monday and Thursday next week from 9 a.m. to noon. Families will receive three meals on Monday and two meals on Thursday. We are consolidating operations to two days to help limit exposure for our volunteers and the need for our families to leave their homes. In the event we are closed beyond next week, we are collaborating with local organizations to consolidate the food distribution to include other community needs. Please help us spread the word!
text: We are hearing rumors in the community that we are discontinuing our meal service. These rumors are false! Our food distribution continues at five sites throughout the district (JP McCaskey, Hand, Reynolds, Carter & MacRae and Hamilton) on Monday and Thursday next week from 9 a.m. to noon. Families will receive three meals on Monday and two meals on Thursday. We are consolidating operations to two days to help limit exposure for our volunteers and the need for our families to leave their homes. In the event we are closed beyond next week, we are collaborating with local organizations to consolidate the food distribution to include other community needs. Please help us spread the word!
